1
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:06,000
National Radio and Television Administration

2
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,240
Come on, let's go to bed.

3
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,840
I'm tired.

4
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:31,570
It's unbelievable.

5
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:34,040
I visited her just a few days ago and she was fine.

6
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,970
And now she's gone, just like that.

7
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,720
Yes, who could have imagined.

8
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,840
Sis, when you went to her house the other day,

9
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,280
was she alone?

10
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,760
Yes, just by herself.

11
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,160
I even said to Qin Gang,

12
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:53,890
why didn't they find someone to keep her company?

13
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,520
I remember Huaming told me

14
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:01,480
she recovered really well after the surgery.

15
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:04,480
If she didn't experience any emotional distress,

16
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:07,210
she could have lived for at least 2 or 3 more years.

17
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:09,280
Do you think it was because

18
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,840
I upset her and made her angry last time?

19
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,320
Don't talk nonsense.

20
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,960
It wasn't your fault.

21
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:17,940
What's wrong, sis?

22
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,600
Nothing.

23
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,079
Don't blame yourself for this.

24
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:28,410
It's not your fault. It has nothing to do with you.

25
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,060
Why don't you go lie down in your room for a while?

26
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,680
Dr. Jia is here. Please come in.

27
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:49,040
Okay.

28
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:58,920
Dr. Jia, thank you for coming.

29
00:03:58,920 --> 00:03:59,920
I just got back from out of town.

30
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,280
Mr. Qin, my condolences.

31
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,940
Thank you. Please have a seat.

32
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,040
I just want to know

33
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,970
why my mother suddenly collapsed.

34
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,620
There are two possibilities.

35
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,880
One is surgical complications.

36
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,720
The other is that she was upset

37
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,050
by emotional distress,

38
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,720
triggering a stroke or heart attack.

39
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:23,640
Liu Wei.

40
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,520
Has my mother contacted you recently?

41
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,120
No.

42
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,820
Why are you asking me this?

43
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,600
I just want to know who could have upset her.

44
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,159
You suspect me?

45
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,720
I'm just asking.

46
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,480
How could you ask me

47
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,409
such questions at a time like this?

48
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,800
You even came looking for me at home that day.

49
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,280
I was home all day.

50
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,840
How could you ask me this?

51
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:48,040
I'm just using process of elimination.

52
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:50,650
If you haven't contacted her, then forget it.

53
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:54,020
Huaming told me the surgery was successful.

54
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:55,400
If things go well,

55
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,880
she could live for two or three more years.

56
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:59,409
But emotional stress is the biggest concern.

57
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:02,850
Who would dare upset her in her condition?

58
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,330
Everyone stayed far away from her.

59
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:09,920
Maybe it was just complications from Huaming's surgery.

60
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,220
That's also possible.

61
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,850
But he doesn't think so.

62
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,880
He suspects I'm the one who upset his mother to death.

63
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,000
I told you I'm just using process of elimination.

64
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,200
Then I should be the first person you eliminate.

65
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,640
Of course I have to suspect you.

66
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:24,800
My mother was fine right after surgery.

67
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,880
How did she suddenly end up like this?

68
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,720
Someone must have upset her.

69
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,880
Who else but you could upset her?

70
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,280
Qin Gang.

71
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,560
How can you say that about me?

72
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,890
The person you should suspect is Huaming.

73
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:37,920
Why?

74
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:41,120
Maybe there was a problem with his surgery.

75
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:44,159
Think about it. He's a quack who has killed patients before.

76
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:45,960
What kind of skills does he have?

77
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,800
A disease that even American experts couldn't cure,

78
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,330
yet he claims he can cure it?

79
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,640
I bet he just wanted to use the surgery

80
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,480
to scam your mother for money.

81
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,140
For that lousy website of his.

82
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,320
Do you even know how qualified he is?

83
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,680
Have you investigated him?

84
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,240
What right do you have to suspect me?

85
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,600
That's not what I meant.

86
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:01,840
Yes, it is.

87
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,280
You are suspecting me.

88
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:04,920
Qin Gang.

89
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,880
If I were the kind of woman who could do such a thing,

90
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:07,720
I would have done it long ago.

91
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,360
Would I have waited until today?

92
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,480
I've had enough.

93
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,170
Where are you going?

94
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:16,460
Can you try to understand me a little?

95
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,960
My mind is in chaos right now.

96
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,290
Of course I'm going to have wild thoughts.

97
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,660
What you said makes sense.

98
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,640
I'll get to the bottom of this.

99
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:49,850
You're leaving?

100
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,810
Where are you going?

101
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,530
I'm going to Shanghai for a research project.

102
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:58,770
You're taking so much stuff just for a research project?

103
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,320
There are too many memories here.

104
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:06,780
I don't want to remember anymore. I need to get away for a while.

105
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,020
You're running away, aren't you?

106
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,130
Why would I be running away?

107
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,860
Do you think the surgery was successful?

108
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:23,220
Then why did my mother suddenly end up like this?

109
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:28,120
Qin Gang, I'm also very sorry about what happened to your mother.

110
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,920
But the surgical plan

111
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:33,360
was personally developed by Dr. Wei in America.

112
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,200
After the surgical plan arrived in China,

113
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,640
your family reviewed and signed off on it.

114
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,360
And I assure you, the surgery

115
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,720
was truly successful.

116
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:43,400
There were no complications after the surgery.

117
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:43,930
I also...

118
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,640
So what you're saying is

119
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,200
I didn't take good care of my mother,

120
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,000
that I made her so angry she died?

121
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,250
That's not what I meant.

122
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:55,000
I'm truly sorry about what happened.

123
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:00,400
Fine.

124
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:04,380
I'm telling you, this matter isn't that simple.

125
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,040
I will get to the bottom of it.

126
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:23,640
I clearly saw Liu Wei coming out of President Qin's house.

127
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:25,720
President Qin must have collapsed from anger because of her.

128
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,720
But you wouldn't let me tell anyone.

129
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,040
You know, since President Qin passed away,

130
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:31,640
I haven't been able to sleep at night.

131
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,280
My conscience is killing me.

132
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:36,880
I understand.

133
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:40,760
But Xu Chunli, you absolutely cannot tell anyone right now.

134
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,890
If you say anything,

135
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,520
I'm finished.

136
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,010
You'll be finished too.

137
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,000
What do you mean?

138
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:51,690
Isn't it just that Liu Wei helped you get your position back?

139
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:52,920
Kaiyang,

140
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,860
are you hiding something from me?

141
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,240
All I can tell you is

142
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:01,040
if anything happens to Liu Wei, I'm in trouble too.

143
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:05,160
What's going on? Tell me now.

144
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,250
It's not the right time to tell you yet.

145
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:16,200
If I go to prison, what will happen to you and our child?

146
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,280
Prison?

147
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,400
What's happening?

148
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,330
You must tell me everything today.

149
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,500
I did something I shouldn't have.

150
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,120
What exactly did you do?

151
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,680
Please don't push me.

152
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,280
If I tell you now...

153
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:34,080
I'll be dragging you into this. Do you understand?

154
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:39,280
Kaiyang, you need to know...

155
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:42,160
No matter how much we argue or fight...

156
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:44,020
We're still husband and wife.

157
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,440
We're the closest people to each other.

158
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,880
If you're not well, I can't be well either.

159
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:50,760
Whatever happens, you need to tell me.

160
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,320
We'll face it together.

161
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:53,440
This situation.

162
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,520
If you feel what you did was wrong...

163
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,640
I'll go with you to turn yourself in.

164
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,440
At worst, when you get out...

165
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,000
We'll be together again.

166
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,490
That's foolish.

167
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,000
If I turn myself in...

168
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,220
Who will pay the mortgage?

169
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:11,240
Where will you live without this house?

170
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:13,810
Who will pay for Xiaoxiao's living expenses?

171
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:18,140
But I can't just watch you make this mistake.

172
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,120
I understand.

173
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:22,300
I promise I'll turn myself in.

174
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,040
But not now.

175
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,120
Let's talk about it in a few days.

176
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,600
I need to go out first.

177
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,360
Kaiyang.

178
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,760
Let's go turn ourselves in now.

179
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:35,320
I'll go with you.

180
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,260
You don't understand.

181
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,780
Some things you do, there's no turning back.

182
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,560
After I finish what I'm doing,

183
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,450
I'll turn myself in.

184
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:57,440
Kaiyang, listen to me.

185
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,140
You must turn yourself in.

186
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,600
You need to hurry up.

187
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:12,780
While Qin Gang and Hua Ming are busy with their lawsuit,

188
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,600
you need to move quickly.

189
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,080
Transfer all the money

190
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,740
to this account immediately.

191
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,450
Why should I do this?

192
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,840
I've helped you plenty of times.

193
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:29,680
Besides, you've always gotten your fair share before.

194
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:30,810
No, it's too little.

195
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:35,040
Without me, you wouldn't get a penny.

196
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:37,480
No, without me,

197
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,080
you wouldn't get a penny.

198
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,280
What do you mean?

199
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,770
Didn't we agree on this before?

200
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,810
How can you back out just like that?

201
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,810
It was because President Qin wasn't dead before.

202
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,010
What do you mean?

203
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:56,260
What does it matter to you whether she's dead or not?

204
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,800
It matters to you.

205
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:01,960
The day President Qin died,

206
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:04,440
my wife saw you leaving her house.

207
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:09,000
Just think if Qin Gang found out his mother

208
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,460
was driven to death by you.

209
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,920
Think about what would happen.

210
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,900
If anything happens to me,

211
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,120
then your scam to cheat him out of his money

212
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,580
won't stay hidden either.

213
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,120
So,

214
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,130
we're in the same boat. Neither of us will come out clean.

215
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,290
What do you want?

216
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:36,680
Half and half.

217
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,680
You're too greedy.

218
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,090
Not negotiable.

219
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:47,960
Fine.

220
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,280
Half and half.

221
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:52,960
But this matter,

222
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,640
you must take care of it for me right away.

223
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:55,900
The sooner the better.

224
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,720
How are you doing?

225
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:43,380
Your mother worried about you the most before she passed away.

226
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:47,050
Did my mom contact you before she died?

227
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:47,840
No.

228
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,260
I was planning to visit your mother that day,

229
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,100
but then...

230
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:58,380
Why are you suddenly asking this?

231
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:00,840
I think

232
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,340
Huaming's surgery is just a scam.

233
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,400
Why would you think that?

234
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:10,240
He just wants to use the surgery funds

235
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,500
to maintain his Huaming Online website.

236
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,460
Think about it.

237
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,850
He didn't treat your father back then,

238
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:17,480
and now he comes back from America

239
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:19,410
with a surgical plan to deceive me.

240
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,480
He's a complete fraud.

241
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,600
He's a quack.

242
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:26,280
Qin Gang, I completely understand how you feel right now.

243
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:29,500
I know you can't accept this reality.

244
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:31,160
But this is the reality.

245
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,680
You can't treat everyone as your enemy.

246
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,400
Enemy?

247
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:39,360
Why are you still so naive?

248
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,580
How can you still believe him?

249
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,260
It was just a coincidence.

250
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:47,010
Could there really be such a coincidence?

251
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,700
I don't want to discuss this with you.

252
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:51,600
Xinxin.

253
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:55,280
From the beginning, he approached you and cared for you

254
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,880
until you fell completely in love with him.

255
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,160
He did all this just to give himself

256
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:59,600
a little comfort.

257
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:02,480
I bet he knew about this from the start.

258
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:04,720
But he's been hiding it from you all along.

259
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,320
It's not what you think.

260
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,160
I don't want to hear any more.

261
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:10,120
He's packing his bags to run away right now.

262
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,880
He's just preparing for a business trip.

263
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:12,880
Wan Xinxin.

264
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,120
I think in this whole world,

265
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,520
you're the only one who still believes him.

266
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:17,840
Just wait.

267
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,880
Wait until I investigate this whole matter.

268
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:22,080
I absolutely won't let him off the hook.

269
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,720
But I need to warn you.

270
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:26,000
If Huaming comes back,

271
00:15:26,040 --> 00:15:27,700
no matter what he says or does,

272
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:30,300
you absolutely cannot let him near Xiaobao.

273
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,080
Because I don't know

274
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,800
what else he might do.

275
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:34,520
Of course,

276
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:36,840
if I find out

277
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,500
